<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Mickle" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Mickle,</orth> much, great: <cit><quote>more m. was the pain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 219" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 219</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the one ne'er got me credit, the other m. blame,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 45</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>an oath of m. might,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 70</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I shall die with m. age,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.6.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 6, 35</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>bows unto the grave with m. age,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.174" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 174</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>m. is the powerful grace,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 3, 15</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>